The paper discusses the design, implementation, and security analysis of an e-voting system, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The system is distributed, fault-tolerant, and uses a bulletin board component, which suggests that it may also fall under the categories of distributed systems (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses privacy-preserving techniques, which may suggest the category of cryptography (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation and performance of the system, which may suggest the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
